# REST Route Pattern

REST endpoints are Hono routes on a per-domain sub-app in
`src/node/routes/{domain}.ts`, mounted by the barrel `routes/index.ts`. There
are no Lambda handlers. A simple authenticated handler follows this shape:

```typescript
import { Hono } from "hono";
import {
  AUDIT_ACTIONS,
  AUDIT_RESOURCE_TYPES,
  AUDIT_STATUS,
  logAudit,
} from "../lib/audit";
import { getUserIdFromClaims } from "../lib/auth";
import { getDb } from "../lib/db";
import { Errors } from "../lib/errors";
import { sendSuccess } from "../lib/hono/respond";
import type { AppEnv } from "../lib/hono/types";
import { createLogger } from "../lib/logger";
import { sanitizeObject } from "../lib/sanitize";
import { parseBody } from "../lib/validation/helpers";
import { resourceSchemas } from "../lib/validation";

export const resource = new Hono<AppEnv>();
const logger = createLogger({ serviceName: "resource-create" });

resource.post("/", async (c) => {
  // requireAuth() (applied in routes/index.ts) has set c.get("claims").
  const userId = await getUserIdFromClaims(c.get("claims")); // async — always await
  const input = parseBody(await c.req.text(), resourceSchemas.create);
  const sanitized = sanitizeObject(input);
  const db = await getDb();
  const [result] = await db.insert(table).values({ ...sanitized, userId }).returning();
  if (!result) throw Errors.InternalServerError();
  void logAudit({
    userId,
    action: AUDIT_ACTIONS.CREATE,
    resourceType: AUDIT_RESOURCE_TYPES.RESOURCE,
    resourceId: result.id,
    ipAddress: c.req.header("cf-connecting-ip"),
    userAgent: c.req.header("user-agent"),
    requestId: c.get("requestId"),
    status: AUDIT_STATUS.SUCCESS,
  });
  return sendSuccess(c, result);
});
```

## Rules
- One Hono sub-app per domain in `routes/{domain}.ts`; add handlers there, not in `app.ts`.
- Mount new domains in `routes/index.ts`. Protect them with `routes.use("/v1/<domain>/*", requireAuth())` in that barrel — never call `requireAuth()` inside the sub-app.
- Auth comes from `requireAuth()`; read verified claims via `c.get("claims")`, then `await getUserIdFromClaims(c.get("claims"))`. Never re-parse JWTs (no `withAuth`, no Lambda authorizer).
- Logging via `createLogger({ serviceName })` from `lib/logger.ts` (NOT AWS Powertools; there is no `logger.addContext`).
- Never try-catch — `app.ts` `onError` formats all errors.
- Always `sanitizeObject()` before a DB write; always `void logAudit()` on mutations (with `c.req.header("cf-connecting-ip")`, `user-agent`, `c.get("requestId")`).
- Return via `sendSuccess(c, data)` (or `createSuccessResponse(data)` inside an idempotency callback); never build a raw `Response`.
- Guard null results: `if (!result) throw Errors.NotFound("Resource")`.
- Non-idempotent mutations: wrap in `withIdempotency({ key, sub, method, path, body, query }, async () => { ... })` (returns a `StoredResponse`; adapt it to a `Response` — see `routes/users.ts` PATCH /me).
- Multi-step reads + writes go in `db.transaction(async (tx) => { ... })`.
- Import validation schemas from `../lib/validation` (barrel) or `../lib/validation/{domain}`.
- Add `@swagger` JSDoc on each endpoint for OpenAPI generation.
- `routes/webhooks.ts` is public and verifies its own signatures; `routes/test.ts` 404s entirely when `STAGE=production`.
